Quick Breath Weapon			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																																																																										PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Ability Focus (breath weapon), breath weapon racial trait, base attack bonus +6.																																																DESC:You can unleash your breath weapon and deliver an attack before your opponent is the wiser.																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:On your turn, you can use your breath weapon in place of one of your melee attacks. You must choose the melee attack with the highest base attack bonus to use your breath weapon. Normal: Using a breath weapon is a standard action.
Reptile Whisperer				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Dragon		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Black																																																																																PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Draconic Heritage (black), dragon character (black sept), or dragon companion (black sept); ability to cast speak with animals.																																								DESC:You speak the language of serpents and commune with them at will.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:You gain a constant speak with animals effect as a spell-like ability, but only to speak with reptilian creatures. If you are a dragon paragon, you can use your speak with animals heritage spell to speak with any animals, not just reptilian animals.
Surprise Breath				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																																																																										PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Breath Weapon Focus, breath weapon racial trait, sneak attack +5d6, base attack bonus +10.																																															DESC:Your breath weapon is especially devastating when you catch your foes off-guard.																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:You can add your sneak attack damage to your breath weapon if the targets are flat-footed. This additional damage only applies to your breath weapon if it is used to deal hit point damage, and the additional damage is of the same type as your breath weapon. If a target succeeds on its saving throw to negate or halve the damage, it also negates or halves the sneak attack damage.
Starflight					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Dragon		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Dragon Sept Outer																																																																															PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (any outer dragon sept) or dragon companion (any outer dragon sept); no breath racial trait.																																											DESC:You can soar throughout the skies with little difficulty.																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:In outer space, you can survive in the void and fly at incredible speeds. Travel times vary, but a trip within a single solar system should take 3d20 hours and a trip beyond should take 3d20 days or more if you know the way to your destination. If you are capable of carrying riders while flying, you can carry one rider of one size category smaller than yourself, four passengers two sizes smaller, eight passengers three sizes smaller, or 16 passengers four or more sizes smaller. Passengers are protected from the void of outer space.
Steeled Scales				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Dragon		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Forest	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Damage Reduction Magic									PRECLASS:1,Dragon Paragon=7																																								PRERACE:1,Dragon														PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character or dragon companion, forest sept, DR/magic class feature, dragon paragon level 7th.																																													DESC:Your scales are tougher than steel and impervious to magic.																															ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Damage Reduction ~ Adamantine													BONUS:VAR|DamageReduction_Adamantine|ParagonDragonDR	BONUS:VAR|DragonParagonDamageReductionMagic|1								SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:Your damage reduction changes from DR/magic to DR/adamantine.
Stony Death					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Dragon		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Forest	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Breath Weapon																									PRELEVEL:MIN=17																																											PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Dragon character (forest sept) or dragon companion (forest sept), breath weapon racial trait, character level 17th.																																										DESC:Your breath transforms its victims into stone statues.																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:Whenever you reduce a creature to 0 or fewer hit points with your breath weapon, the creature is immediately petrified, as flesh to stone, unless it succeeds on a Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 your dragon paragon level + your Charisma modifier). This ability is a death effect.
Trackless Presence			CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Dragon		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Woodland Stride Heritage																																																																														PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Woodland stride heritage power.																																																								DESC:If you are impossible to track if you don't wish to be found.																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:You leave no trail in natural surroundings and cannot be tracked. You may wish to leave a trail if so desired.
True Courage				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Dragon		PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Diehard,Endurance	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Dragon Sept ~ Silver																											PRELEVEL:MIN=17																																											PRETEXT:Prerequisites: Diehard, Endurance, 17 HD, dragon character (silver sept).																																																				DESC:You continue fighting long after others would have faltered.																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.35	BENEFIT:While you are at 0 or fewer hit points, you do not lose 1 hit point when you take an action (though you are still staggered). If you take damage or are the target of a spell that causes your death, you remain alive for 1 round and can act normally (you are not staggered for this final round).
